  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-head"><span class="section-pill">FAQs</span><h2>Quick answers</h2></div>
    <div class="faq-list">
      <details><summary>What is Udyam and why do I need it?</summary><p>Udyam is the Govt of India's MSME registration. It officially classifies your business as Micro / Small / Medium and gives you access to schemes like MUDRA loans, lower bank interest rates, govt tender bidding, and procurement preference.</p></details>
      <details><summary>Isn't Udyam free on the govt portal?</summary><p>Yes, the portal charges nothing. ₹999/- is our service fee for getting it done correctly - right NIC code, right classification, no rejections. Many DIY attempts fail due to mismatch with Aadhaar/PAN data.</p></details>
      <details><summary>How long does it take?</summary><p>Most certificates issue within 24 hours of payment. In rare cases (Aadhaar mismatch), we co-ordinate with you and resubmit - takes 2-3 days.</p></details>
      <details><summary>Do I need GST first?</summary><p>No. Udyam can be obtained independently. Many businesses get Udyam BEFORE GST to access startup-friendly schemes.</p></details>
      <details><summary>Can I cancel and get a refund?</summary><p>Yes &mdash; full refund within 24 hours of payment if not yet filed. After filing, the govt fee is non-refundable.</p></details>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

